programme.title: My Lottery Dream Home
programme.desc: David Bromstad is in Loxahatchee, FL, to help find the perfect horse ranch for a family who won a staggering $5 million on a Florida scratchie.

programme.title: My Lottery Dream Home
programme.desc: Ashley joined a work colleague taking a chance on lottery scratchers, and it paid off. Now David Bromstad is helping her buy her first home in Cape Girardeau, MO, with her $1 million winnings.

programme.title: Property Brothers: Forever Home
programme.desc: After landing a historic home in the LA neighbourhood of their dreams, Emily and Adhir discover that their Spanish Revival style forever home is in worse shape than they thought.

programme.title: George Clarkes Amazing Spaces
programme.desc: George travels to North Yorkshire to meet couple Paul and Rachel, who want to bring together their mutual loves of the railway and gin, by transforming an old goods wagon into a summerhouse.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: What Happened Next?
programme.desc: Our property experts catch up with house-hunters who bought their perfect place abroad, and get a glimpse of what their lives are like living in the sun.

programme.title: My Dream Home
programme.desc: Angie and Tito are living in a cramped apartment full of their kids toys. Even their car doubles as storage. They want a large modern house, close to downtown, with a gourmet kitchen and hardwood floors.

programme.title: Love It or List It Vancouver
programme.desc: Michele, Brent and their adult children are sick of fighting for space in their dysfunctional home. Can Jillian create peace with an open concept redesign or will Todd find a move-in-ready home with enough space?

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: After 30 years of living in Manchester, Clover and Mark have decided its time to find a new home and start a new life in the stunning white villages of Axarquia in Andalucia.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Ben Hillman is house hunting with Steph and Ian, who are looking for their dream holiday home on the Central Algarve for an ideal budget of 280,000 pounds.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Ben Hillman is with Lisa and Neil, showing them five properties around Costa Calida in south-east Spain for their budget of 100,000 pounds.

programme.title: Seeds of Yesterday
programme.desc: The saga of the tormented Dollangangers comes to an end where the family continues to coexist miserably. The film follows Cathys two adult sons, Bart and Jory half-brothers with little in common whose lives are fuelled by deeply troubled relationships, dark secrets and misfortune that come to a head in a way that will haunt the family and its progeny forever.

programme.title: I Was Octomom
programme.desc: In 2009, Natalie Suleman gives birth to eight children with the help of IVF, only to have her life torn apart, and her identity rebranded by the media.

programme.title: Vanished in Death Valley
programme.desc: A teenage girl goes missing after her familys car breaks down in Death Valley. Her parents soon find some unexpected help as they embark on a desperate search to find her.

programme.title: Who Is Killing The Cheerleaders?
programme.desc: Ellie, a former cheerleader, returns to her high school as a teacher ten years after she was nearly killed in a series of brutal slayings on the squad. When the attacks start up again shortly after her arrival, she must find the killer before they get to her first.

programme.title: My Sisters Serial Killer Boyfriend
programme.desc: Maddie, a local reporter investigating a series of killings targeting similar looking women is caught off guard when her younger sister Olivia, is attacked in her own home. Urging on the side of caution, Maddie suggests they take a self defence course. When Olivia starts to fall for their instructor, Maddie becomes sceptical when he refuses to reveal anything about himself, and tries to intervene before the relationship turns into a deadly obsession.

programme.title: Single Black Female 3: The Final Chapter
programme.desc: Monica is proven innocent after being wrongfully arrested for murder. As charges are dropped, the police shift focus to Simone, who has vanished while bonding with her daughter Joy.

programme.title: The Killer I Picked Up
programme.desc: When a hardworking single mother starts a side job as a ride share driver to help pay for her daughters college tuition, she becomes the unrelenting obsession of a mysterious rider with a dark past.

programme.title: Abducted In The Everglades
programme.desc: A college student vanishes during spring break in Miami. Her mother, with help from a local boatman, braves dangers to urgently search for her and unravel the mystery.

programme.title: Expecting Amish
programme.desc: When an eventful Rumspringa leads to an unintended pregnancy, Amish teen Hannah must choose between returning to faith and family or beginning a new life elsewhere.

programme.title: Envy: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Gabrielle Flores has it all - a devoted husband, a beautiful daughter, and one of the best PR firms in the country. When Gabrielles father suddenly reveals she has a half-sister, Keisha, as a result of a brief affair, only - child Gabrielle is delighted to welcome her into her life. But Keisha, who grew up with nothing, wants more than a sisterly bond from Gabrielle - she wants her life, and is willing to do whatever it takes to get it.

programme.title: To Have and to Hold
programme.desc: Alice, who still cant believe her high school crush, the dashing, wealthy and successful Joe, would choose to marry her, willingly allows him to mould her into his ideal socialite wife. Despite Alices best efforts to be the woman of Joes dreams, he cant help but be unfaithful to her. When Joes indiscretions impact his career, Alices life is further turned upside down. Alice unexpectedly finds herself falling for her best friend Emilys boyfriend Harry and begins to wonder if her fairy tale ending could exist after all.

programme.title: Nightmare Tenant
programme.desc: When a woman rents out her college-bound daughters room to a young woman, she doesnt realise that the girl is her daughters vengeful high school rival.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Pearl In The Mist
programme.desc: Fate whisked Ruby from a simple life in the Louisiana Bayou. But her new riches bring more treachery than happiness. Even after a year as a Dumas, Ruby still wonders at the splendor of the familys New Orleans mansion and rejoices in the love of the father she had never known. But true happiness in her new home is as elusive as the swamp mist. Ruby must carefully avoid her venomous stepmother, Daphne, while making every effort to befriend her twin sister, Gisselle. While attending Greenwood, the exclusive girls boarding school, Ruby doesnt lose hope in a world that never really wanted her. Ruby will have to summon every last ounce of her Cajun strength to reclaim her home, her future, and the happiness she once knew.

programme.title: Single Black Female 2
programme.desc: Three years after narrowly escaping the murderous clutches of her half-sister Simone, Monica is ready for a fresh start in Seattle as the host of the citys number one prime-time investigative program.

programme.title: The Lover in the Attic: A True Story
programme.desc: This is the lurid, true story about femme fatale Dolly, her murdered husband, and her lover, Otto - the man in the attic. In the 1930s, Dolly met and seduced her repairman Otto but she was already married to successful business man Fred. Their affair grew so strong that she decided to move him into her attic and keep him as her sex slave, unbeknownst to Fred. Otto lived in Dollys attic for four years, even moving houses with them, until one night during a heated argument between Dolly and Fred, Otto burst downstairs from the attic and killed Fred. Now the two must cover up the murder and try to live a normal life, but will they be able to keep their secret?

programme.title: Girl in the Box
programme.desc: In 1977, 22-year-old Colleen Stan doesnt think twice when she hitch hikes and is picked up by a young couple, Cameron and Janice Hooker. But the life she knows is completely ripped away when the couple abducts her and takes her to their home where Cameron tortures and sexually abuses her. For the next seven years, Colleen is imprisoned for up to 23 hours a day, in a coffin-sized box hidden beneath the couples bed. When not incarcerated, Colleen is part of a strange new life as a live-in slave, babysitter, and victim of Camerons bizarre and extreme sexual fantasies.

programme.title: Murder At The Lighthouse
programme.desc: Fleeing her abusive ex, Jess hires a boat to Canada, but when it sinks, shes rescued by a reclusive lighthouse keeper. As she heals, Jess realises shes fallen into another trap.

programme.title: Murder at the Derby
programme.desc: Kara lands her dream job at a prestigious horse stable under Jennifers mentorship, but tensions rise when Jennifers jealous brother puts everyones lives at risk.

programme.title: No One Would Tell
programme.desc: Laura Collins (Shannen Doherty), single mum to daughter Sarah (Matreya Scarrwener), has had a history of rocky relationships, so when Sarah begins dating the popular and charismatic Rob Tennison (Callan Potter), Laura is thrilled with what she sees. But when it becomes increasingly clear that Rob has a darker, possessive side, Laura lives in a state of denial about her daughters relationship until Sarah goes missing. Laura must find the will to fight for justice for Sarah when a case against Rob is brought to trial and presided over by a powerful judge (Mira Sorvino).

programme.title: Surviving The Sleepover
programme.desc: Outspoken teenager Hannah goes to a sleepover at a popular girls house, not realising she was only invited to be the victim of a prank.

programme.title: A Deadly Threat to My Family
programme.desc: Marielle becomes suspicious when her sister-in-law escapes from a cult and seeks refuge at her home. When another cult member shows up on her doorstep, she fears her daughter is their next target.

programme.title: Beaches
programme.desc: While remaining faithful to the original story, we follow the lifelong friendship between LA-born CC Bloom and San Francisco rich girl Hillary Whitney after they serendipitously meet on Venice Beach. In this update, CC is a budding pop star who is struggling to make it in LA until she is discovered by a music producer who helps her develop her raw talent. Hillary is the daughter of a prominent lawyer who is intent on making her own destiny and getting out from under the control of her domineering father. Their friendship - even with its ups and downs - sustains them for decades, but ends tragically with Hillarys early death.

programme.title: Wife Stalker
programme.desc: Joannas obsessive fantasy of a perfect life with Leo shatters, forcing her to confront harsh reality and the truth about their relationship, with dire consequences.

programme.title: Watch Your Back
programme.desc: A woman and her husband become increasingly scared as an anonymous person begins stalking their family.

programme.title: Ill Be Watching
programme.desc: Based on the novel The Purple Rose by Christi R. Walsh. After narrowly escaping the clutches of a deadly stalker, a beautiful young woman flees to a remote anonymous town, where she rebuilds her life and finds the man of her dreams, until the man of her nightmares tracks her down.

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas mans execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Road Trip Hostage
programme.desc: A deranged criminal forces a young woman to drive him across the country.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews All That Glitters
programme.desc: Driven from the Dumas Mansion back to her beloved bayou, Ruby is determined to make a secure and happy home for her precious infant daughter, Pearl. Paul Tate, her first love, is at her side once more with dazzling wealth. Whisking her into his grand house, it seems their future is assured. But the thick, expensive walls of Cypress Woods cannot shut out the terrible memories and shocking reasons that have woven their fabric over her destiny, or the cold eyes of Pauls mother, Gladys, reminding Ruby of the secret she must keep to give Pearl a loving father. Desperate to find the complete, fulfilling life she craves, Ruby builds a precarious new existence, a flimsy shanty of hope that the first flood washes away. Only when the storm exposes the very blackest evils of the past will she glimpse the rainbows fragile promise, a morning of sunshine and laughter with a family of her own.

programme.title: From Straight As to XXX
programme.desc: Based on the true story of Duke University student Miriam Weeks, also known as Belle Knox. From Straight As to XXX tells the true story of Miriam Weeks, who as a freshman at Duke University looking to make money to cover tuition, became infamously known for starring in online pornography under the pseudonym, Belle Knox. The Miriam Weeks/ Belle Knox story represents the hypocrisy of "slut-shaming." Portrayed as neither a villain nor a hero, Belle Knox is a young woman who made a choice that changed her life forever.

programme.title: Sisters
programme.desc: A reporter who witnesses a brutal murder becomes entangled in a mystery involving conjoined twins who were separated at birth.

programme.title: If There Be Thorns
programme.desc: With Christopher and Cathy Dollanganger living together as man and wife, Cathys two sons are unaware of the incestuous nature of their parents relationship. But when a mysterious woman moves in next door and befriends the younger boy, Bart, he begins a strange transformation and displays accusatory behaviour towards Cathy and Christopher. When Christopher discovers their mysterious neighbour is, in fact, his mother Corrine Dollanganger, all of the familys long-hidden secrets are revealed in a tragic climax.

programme.title: Britney Ever After
programme.desc: This is the tumultuous true story of Britney Jean Spears, one of the bestselling teenage music artists of all-time, whose dating life and public emotional breakdowns were the subjects of a worldwide media frenzy. By the age of 21, Britney Spears already had a number one platinum, debut album, a cover on Rolling Stone, a record-breaking second album, and international superstardom. Success in her personal life, however, would be much harder to achieve. A well-publicized romance and break-up with Justin Timberlake, a three-day marriage to a childhood sweetheart, and an ill-fated marriage to back-up dancer Kevin Federline made for a chaotic contrast to her record-setting music career.

programme.title: Menendez: Blood Brothers
programme.desc: Erik and Lyle Menendez were educated, nice boys from sunny Beverly Hills, California. Erik was an exceptional tennis player and Lyle was studying at Princeton University. So when their parents were found shot dead in their home, no one could figure out why they would have done it? Everyone was perplexed. Was it for Money? For Fame? The case seemed closed, but that;s when the brothers revealed that they were sexually molested throughout their childhoods by their father, Jose. This was the trial that no one was ready for. Our story follows Erik and Lyle as they struggle with their overwhelming guilt, the harsh reality of abuse, incest and molestation that lead them down this path and the trial that shocked an entire nation of television watchers. Never before seen details emerge as we look closer into the lives of the Menendez brothers.

programme.title: The Bear Lake Murders
programme.desc: A sheriff teams up with a detective to uncover the truth behind a series of annual deaths in a resort town. Their investigation leads them to believe that a killer is preying on holidaymakers.

programme.title: Oscar Pistorius: Blade Runner Killer
programme.desc: The true story of the sprint runner dubbed theBlade Runner; and his rise to fame as a gold medalist Paralympic champion and as the first double-leg amputee to participate in the Olympics. Oscars resilience to overcome his disability combined with his apparent fairy tale relationship with model Reeva Steenkap turned him into a media favorite. This all shattered one Valentines Day night when four bullets were fired and Reevas life was taken. Her brutal death shocked the world and the court room drama that followed consumed the news.

programme.title: Nightmare in the Desert
programme.desc: A woman returns home hoping to move on, but finds herself fighting for survival in the desert when someone tries to prevent her boyfriends surprise proposal, even through murder.

programme.title: Close Calls: On Camera
programme.desc: Presented by Nick Knowles, this series brings to life the stories of ordinary people who have faced extraordinary circumstances - emergencies, accidents and incidents. With access to a variety of sources such as video and phone footage shot by the victims and onlookers, dramatic real-life 999 calls, and first-hand accounts from the victims and their friends and families, Close Calls: On Camera relives the split-second moments when everyday events are transformed into disasters and meets the people who lived to tell the tale. Watch the terrifying moment that a mother and her two children are suddenly faced with a life-threatening decision when their car starts burning uncontrollably in a Safari Park lion enclosure, or witness when a day of skiing takes a terrifying turn for three friends, after one of them misjudges the track and disappears into a bottomless crack in the ice.

programme.desc: In tonights show we revisit Josh who came to the clinic after suffering from night terrors which were making him talk and shout obscenities in his sleep causing severe sleep deprivation to himself and his distressed wife. With their relationship on the rocks Josh underwent treatment at a sleep clinic and is coming back to the clinic to let Dr Dawn how he and his long suffering wife have been getting on since his treatment. We also revisit Elizabeth who underwent surgery to remove her rotten toenail, we catch up with Lois who suffered for years from persistent thrush. After a series of tests after the programme she was diagnosed with a thyroid problem. Dr Christian also catches up with Brian who came to see him with leaking bowels. After a change of diet and lifestyle we find out if Brian has managed to wipe out his problem for good and we catch up with Barry who underwent surgery for Prostate cancer. The doctors also delve into the world of labia shape and size and use the Embarrassing Bodies website to show worried females that there really is nothing to worry about.

programme.title: Close Calls: On Camera
programme.desc: Presented by Nick Knowles, this series brings to life the stories of ordinary people who have faced extraordinary circumstances - emergencies, accidents and incidents. With access to a variety of sources such as video and phone footage shot by the victims and onlookers, dramatic real-life 999 calls, and first-hand accounts from the victims and their friends and families, Close Calls: On Camera relives the split-second moments when everyday events are transformed into disasters and meets the people who lived to tell the tale. Watch the terrifying moment that a mother and her two children are suddenly faced with a life-threatening decision when their car starts burning uncontrollably in a Safari Park lion enclosure, or witness when a day of skiing takes a terrifying turn for three friends, after one of them misjudges the track and disappears into a bottomless crack in the ice.

programme.title: Single White Female
programme.desc: Hedy Carlson and Allie Jones - two women taken to their most primal extremes from which only one can emerge. When Allie throws out her two-timing boyfriend, Hedy suddenly appears to help her fight off the urges to call him back. The surviving half of a set of twins, Hedy seeks someone to complete her, and sees in the chic and articulate Allie everything she would like to be so she not only moves into the apartment, but into the most personal aspects of Allies life, even going so far as to have her hair styled the same. But when Allie reconciles with her boyfriend, their unspoken bargain goes terrifyingly awry. Instincts dont come baser than this.

When new Indigenous inmate Tasha is put under Doreens care, Ferguson sees an opportunity to force Kaz into action against Bea. With Maxine as acting top dog, Ferguson places Tasha in Lucys orbit and when Tasha breaks the rules by protecting herself from Lucys molestation, Maxine appears to have no choice but to punish Tasha. Ferguson urges Kaz to stand up to Maxine and save the innocent girl from abuse at the hands of a man, thereby tapping into Kazs past trauma. Bea and Allys bond is cemented when they are slotted in adjoining cells and spend hours talking.
